From wikipedia : The differences between loggers and drillers depths are due to different stretch in the drilling string when drilling, and the wire line entered into the bore hole during wireline logging operations. This difference is estimated and referred to as "core shift". A core from a certain drillers depth is lined up with a wireline log (loggers depth) and structures in the core are compared with the log and matched.

COLLOCATED: Stricter version of EQUIVALENT, in which objects "should be the same" in space. PREVIOUSLY_COLLOCATED: Indicates that two objects were COLLOCATED at some time in the past.
